{"type":"step-attempt","step":"design","sessionId":"c5de5afb-e8db-496f-98af-e445d4484829","outcome":{"verdict":"success","findingsPath":null,"error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"reason":"Wrote design.md, spec.md, and tasks.md under specrunner/changes/repo-root-entry-resolution/ on branch change/repo-root-entry-resolution-3cedb338.\n\nDesign summary: resolve repo root once at dispatch (bin/specrunner.ts) and inject a CommandContext { repoRoot, invokerCwd } into handlers; add a requiresRepo declaration on CommandDef with a unified out-of-repo error (repoRequiredError, exit 2). Convert the three symptom paths — request new (command-registry:334 → ctx.repoRoot, requiresRepo:true), job stats (:683 → ctx.repoRoot, requiresRepo:true), and doctor (DoctorContext gains optional repoRoot; 9 repo/storage checks derive base from ctx.repoRoot ?? ctx.cwd; doctor stays requiresRepo:false so it runs outside a repo). Preserve role (b) relative-path resolution (validate arg / --prompt-file) and worktree semantics (resolveRepoRoot returns enclosing worktree root, unchanged). Add a src/-wide process.cwd() allowlist ratchet (new CWD invariant in core-invariants.test.ts + arch-allowlist.ts seed of ~40 current occurrences classified permanent-legit vs debt), following the existing delete-only, CODEOWNERS-gated governance.\n\nTasks T-01..T-07 map to acceptance criteria T1–T7, each with acceptance criteria and mutation checks; tasks.md includes an enumerated allowlist seed appendix. Verified all cited file:line assertions against the current tree during design; used the existing main() dispatch test harness and runChecks/runJobStats/executeNew seams to keep the criteria testable without breaking existing unit tests.","status":"success"},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-20T03:33:14.522Z","endedAt":"2026-07-20T03:49:04.654Z","commitOid":"f2e796e2f59e3e57cd834737825f52189e6d2bb2"}
